OL,3,CYet another heat record broken as
OL,4,Ctemperatures continue to soar
OL,6,FTemperatures look set to break yet
OL,7,Fanother record as the South grapples
OL,8,Fwith the third heatwave of the year.
OL,10,FForecasters recorded 34C at Larkhill
OL,11,Fin Wiltshire on Friday (10 July),
OL,12,Fmaking it the most number of days the
OL,13,FUK has seen temperatures reach or
OL,14,Fexceed 34C in a calendar year.
OL,16,FOn Thursday (9 July) a high of 34.4C
OL,17,Fwas recorded at Wisley in Surrey,
OL,18,Fbreaking the previous record of seven
OL,19,Fdays set in both the infamous summer
OL,20,Fof 1976 and 2020.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/6
