OL,3,CYet another heat record broken as
OL,4,Ctemperatures continue to soar
OL,6,FAnother temperature topping day today
OL,7,Fwould take the record to nine days and
OL,8,Fit could well be broken again with
OL,9,Fmore hot weather on the way.
OL,11,FAmber heat-health alerts are now in
OL,12,Fplace across most of England,
OL,13,Fincluding the South East and South
OL,14,FWest. The UK Health Security Agency
OL,15,Fsays it will remain in place until 9pm
OL,16,Fon Sunday 12 July.
OL,18,FConditions have led to hosepipe bans
OL,19,Fand early harvests as well as wider
OL,20,Fimpacts on health, energy, wildfire
OL,21,Frisks and transport.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
