OL,3,CYet another heat record broken as
OL,4,Ctemperatures continue to soar
OL,6,FSouth East Water introduced a ban on
OL,7,FJuly 3 for areas of Kent, including
OL,8,Fthose in Ashford, Canterbury,
OL,9,FFaversham, Maidstone, Sevenoaks,
OL,10,FSnodland, Tenterden and Tunbridge
OL,11,FWells.
OL,13,FAnd hosepipe restrictions came into
OL,14,Fforce today (July 10) for about one
OL,15,Fmillion Southern Water customers
OL,16,Facross Hampshire and the Isle of Wight.
OL,18,FWith temperatures expected to remain
OL,19,Fhigh throughout next week, South East
OL,20,FCoast Ambulance Service is warning
OL,21,Fit's under increasing pressure.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
