CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1783711191
OL,3,CYet another heat record broken as
OL,4,Ctemperatures continue to soar
OL,6,FAnd families, neighbours and carers
OL,7,Fare being urged to check in on people
OL,8,Fliving with dementia, who can face
OL,9,Fserious risks from hot weather.
OL,11,FScientists say these record-breaking
OL,12,Fweather events are becoming more
OL,13,Fintense and more frequent because of
OL,14,Fclimate change, largely driven by the
OL,15,Fburning of fossil fuels.
OL,17,FAs people try to stay cool, one man
OL,18,Fwho runs an air conditioning
OL,19,Finstallation company in Brighton says
OL,20,Fthe phone has not stopped ringing.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
